pullRequest.body:
Let `R` be a commutative ring and `A` and `B` two `R`-algebras.
- `Subalgebra.centralizer_sup`: if `S` and `T` are subalgebras of `A`, then the centralizer of `S âŠ” T` is the intersection of the centralizer of `S` and the centralizer of `T`.
- `Subalgebra.centralizer_range_includeLeft_eq_center_tensorProduct`: if `B` is free as a module, then the centralizer of `A` in `A âŠ— B` is `C(A) âŠ— B` where `C(A)` is the center of `A`.
- `Subalgebra.centralizer_range_includeRight_eq_center_tensorProduct`: if `A` is free as a module, then the centralizer of `B` in `A âŠ— B` is `A âŠ— C(B)` where `C(B)` is the center of `B`.
